        <li id="en9">The logic extends to cases more uncomfortable than this one. A gift intended for food, spent instead on crack cocaine by someone for whom that was the genuine pressing need: [CHA]&rsquo;s felicity condition is still satisfied. The mode does not evaluate the recipient&rsquo;s choices. That is [MOR]&rsquo;s jurisdiction. [CHA] asks only whether the need that existed was met.</li>
